{"id": "EUVD-2025-15854", "enisaUuid": "39a29ebb-ab8e-3460-a428-8f4e5d207100", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nwifi: cfg80211: fix out-of-bounds access during multi-link element defragmentation\n\nCurrently during the multi-link element defragmentation process, the\nmulti-link element length added to the total IEs length when calculating\nthe length of remaining IEs after the multi-link element in\ncfg80211_defrag_mle(). This could lead to out-of-bounds access if the\nmulti-link element or its corresponding fragment elements are the last\nelements in the IEs buffer.\n\nTo address this issue, correctly calculate the remaining IEs length by\ndeducting the multi-link element end offset from total IEs end offset.", "datePublished": "2025-05-20T18:30:57", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-14T18:31:19", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/73dde269a1a43e6b1aa92eba13ad2df58bfdd38e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9423f6da825172b8dc60d4688ed3d147291c3be9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e1c6d0c6199bd5f4cfc7a66ae7032b6e805f904d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/023c1f2f0609218103cbcb48e0104b144d4a16dc", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37973"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37973"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2952b964-1622-33b0-995e-994f0304536e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2481b5da9c6b2ee1fde55a1c29eb2ca377145a10 <73dde269a1a43e6b1aa92eba13ad2df58bfdd38e"}, {"id": "5728eae9-ea99-339e-adb2-ed8d0ac2f9ec", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2481b5da9c6b2ee1fde55a1c29eb2ca377145a10 <9423f6da825172b8dc60d4688ed3d147291c3be9"}, {"id": "736ccf17-5334-387a-b187-67f4cdda2eed", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15-rc6"}, {"id": "77b61679-3454-3c9e-ae1b-5fcd7f5623d5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2481b5da9c6b2ee1fde55a1c29eb2ca377145a10 <e1c6d0c6199bd5f4cfc7a66ae7032b6e805f904d"}, {"id": 